<http://example.org/tennis/player/Andy_Murray> a ns2:Player ;
    rdfs:label "Andy Murray" ;
    ns2:playedAgainst <http://example.org/tennis/player/Carlos_Alcaraz>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/David_Ferrer>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Del_Potro>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Fognini>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Guillermo_Canas>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Jo_Wilfried_Tsonga>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/John_Isner>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Juan_Martin_del_Potro>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Novak_Djokovic>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Rafa_Nadal>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Rafael_Nadal>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Roger_Federer>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/player/Stan_Wawrinka> ;
    ns2:won <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/French_Open>,
        <http://example.org/tennis/tournament/Wimbledon_Championships> ;
    ns3:evidenceText "\"Andy Murray battles back to beat Carlos Alcaraz at Indian Wells\".",
        "\"Andy Murray beaten by Novak Djokovic in Australian Open final\".",
        "- \"Andy Murray beats Novak Djokovic to win ATP World Tour Finals, tops men's rankings\".",
        "- \"Andy Murray beats Rafa Nadal despite awful troubles with serve in Madrid Masters semi-final\".",
        "- \"Andy Murray beats Rafael Nadal to win Madrid Masters final\".",
        "Djokovic won the French Open, defeating Murray in four sets, completing the historic Nole Slam.[186][187]",
        "He beat Jo-Wilfried Tsonga to reach the semifinals but lost to Murray and then to Juan Martín del Potro in the bronze medal match, finishing fourth.",
        "In Miami, he defeated Rafael Nadal in the quarterfinals, Andy Murray in the semifinals, and Guillermo Cañas in the final, earning his first Masters title and becoming the youngest male champion in the history of the tournament.[52]",
        "No British man won the singles event at Wimbledon between Fred Perry in 1936 and Andy Murray in 2013, while no British woman has won since Virginia Wade in 1977, although Annabel Croft and Laura Robson won the Girls' Championship in 1984 and 2008 respectively.",
        "Other notable players who have won multiple Grand Slam events but have never won the French Open, includes John McEnroe, Jimmy Connors, John Newcombe, Venus Williams, Stefan Edberg, Virginia Wade, Boris Becker, Andy Murray, Louise Brough, and Martina" ;
    ns3:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Alcaraz"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/French_Open"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rafael_Nadal"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wimbledon_Championships"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    owl:sameAs <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q33837> .

