    ns3:evidenceText "\"Alcaraz fights back to beat Sinner in all-time classic French Open men's final – as it happened\".",
        "\"Alcaraz survives match point to beat Ramos Viñolas in marathon\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz Recently Beat Nadal and Djokovic on Clay.",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz beats Frances Tiafoe in five-set thriller to reach US Open final\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz follows Federer's 2015 path to US Open final, beats Djokovic without dropping a set\".",
        "\"Carlos Alcaraz sees psychologist in bid to beat Novak Djokovic on Centre Court\".",
        "- \"ATP Finals results 2023: Novak Djokovic beats Carlos Alcaraz to set up Jannik Sinner final\".",
        "- \"Barcelona Open: Carlos Alcaraz beats Stefanos Tsitsipas to retain title\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz Beats Giulio Zeppieri to Reach Umag Final\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Alexander Zverev to take Madrid Open title\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Novak Djokovic to win Wimbledon title in final for the ages\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in Barcelona Open thriller to guarantee spot in world's top-10\".",
        "- \"Carlos Alcaraz: World number one withdraws from Spain's Davis Cup Finals team\".",
        "- \"China Open: Carlos Alcaraz recovers to beat Jannik Sinner in dramatic final\".",
        "- \"French Open 2025 results: Carlos Alcaraz fights back to beat Jannik Sinner in classic Roland Garros final\".",
        "- \"US Open 2025 results: How Carlos Alcaraz produced 'faultless' performance to beat Jannik Sinner and win title\".",
        "Alcaraz beat top seed Stefanos Tsitsipas in the quarterfinals of the Barcelona Open to enter the world top 10 for the first time on 25 April 2022.[81][82]",
        "Alcaraz comfortably reached the final of the Barcelona Open, where he lost to Holger Rune.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Alexander Zverev in another five-setter to claim his first Roland Garros title.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Félix Auger-Aliassime in the semifinal, making only three unforced errors in the first set.",
        "Alcaraz defeated Jiří Lehečka in the final to claim his third consecutive title, and fifth title of the season.[208]",
        "Alcaraz defeated Pablo Carreño Busta to win the Barcelona title.[85]",
        "Alcaraz defeated world No. 1 Jannik Sinner to claim his first Italian Open title.",
        "Alcaraz easily qualified for the French Open and reached the third round, where he was defeated by Jan-Lennard Struff.",
        "Alcaraz entered the Challenger Oeiras III as an unseeded player, and defeated Facundo Bagnis in the final to claim the fourth Challenger title of his career.[54][55]",
        "Alcaraz made appearances in both seasons of Netflix's Break Point docuseries,[319] and played against Rafael Nadal in The Netflix Slam, a live-streamed tennis match hosted by MGM Resorts International on March 3, 2024.[320]",
        "Alcaraz won their first major final at the French Open, despite Sinner holding three championship points in the fourth set.",
        "As the main draw was postponed due to the COVID-19 pandemic, Alcaraz played the Great Ocean Road Open in early February, where he was defeated by Thiago Monteiro.[46]",
        "As the two-time defending champion at Indian Wells, Alcaraz lost to Jack Draper in the semifinals despite bagelling him in the second set.",
        "At Indian Wells, Alcaraz defeated defending champion Cameron Norrie to reach his first Masters quarterfinal and semifinal, which he lost to Rafael Nadal.[78]",
        "At Wimbledon, Alcaraz lost to Jannik Sinner in the fourth round.[97]",
        "At the French Open, Djokovic defeated world No. 1 Carlos Alcaraz in the semis and beat Casper Ruud in the final to win a record-breaking 23rd major, becoming the first man to achieve a triple Career Grand Slam.[284",
        "At the Queen's Club, Alcaraz claimed his first title on grass in just his third Tour-level grass tournament, beating Alex de Minaur in the final.",
        "At the Vienna Open two weeks later, Alcaraz met Murray for a rematch and defeated him.[68]",
        "Both players met again in the quarterfinals of 2025 Australian Open, in which Djokovic won in four sets[377] and in the semifinals of 2025 US Open, in which Alcaraz won in straight sets.",
        "Carlos Alcaraz defeated four-time defending champion Novak Djokovic in the final, 1–6, 7–6(8–6), 6–1, 3–6, 6–4 to win the gentlemen's singles tennis title at the 2023 Wimbledon Championships.",
        "In 2022, Alcaraz won his first major title at the US Open.",
        "In 2026, Alcaraz won the Australian Open, becoming the youngest man in history to complete the Career Grand Slam, at 22 years, 8 months and 27 days old.",
        "In September 2020, aged 17, Alcaraz played his first qualifying round at a major tournament at the postponed French Open.",
        "In his first main draw match at the Australian Open, Alcaraz defeated fellow qualifier Botic van de Zandschulp in straight sets.",
        "In the first round of Wimbledon, Alcaraz was unexpectedly taken to five sets by Fabio Fognini, who had already announced his retirement and had not won a match all season.[209]",
        "In the second round, Alcaraz was defeated by Mikael Ymer.",
        "In the third round of the US Open, Alcaraz defeated world No. 3 Stefanos Tsitsipas in a dramatic fifth-set tiebreak on Arthur Ashe Stadium.[63]",
        "Notable early matches include the 2022 US Open quarterfinal, which Alcaraz won en route to the title in five sets after saving a match point.[235]",
        "The day after his 19th birthday, Alcaraz defeated five-time champion, world No. 4 and third seed Rafael Nadal in the quarterfinals of the Madrid Open.[86]",
        "The duo soon met for a rematch in the 2023 Wimbledon final, in which Alcaraz defeated four-time defending champion Djokovic in an epic five-setter that lasted 4 hours and 42 minutes.[255]",
        "They had further high profile encounters in the quarterfinals of the 2023 US Open, won by Alcaraz, and the quarterfinals of the 2024 Australian Open, won by Zverev.",
        "They met again at Wimbledon, where Sinner won in four sets, dethroning defending champion Alcaraz; and at the US Open, where Alcaraz won in four sets, dethroning defending champion Sinner.[238]",
        "They would meet again soon after in the 2023 Wimbledon final, in which Alcaraz defeated Djokovic in an epic five-setter that lasted 4 hours and 42 minutes, ending his hopes for the calendar Grand Slam and his decade-long, record 45-match Centre Court win streak.[370]",
        "Two weeks later, at the Miami Open, Alcaraz defeated Casper Ruud to win his first Masters title.",
        "Zverev won the next two sets in a pair of tiebreaks, but Alcaraz recovered in time to win the fifth set, proceeding to his maiden Australian Open final." ;
    ns3:sourceURL "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2023_Wimbledon_Championships_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_singles"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carlos_Alcaraz"^^xsd:anyURI,
        "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Novak_Djokovic"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    owl:sameAs <http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q85518537> .

