    ns3:evidenceText "\"Djokovic beats Ferrer to win Dubai Championships\".",
        "\"Djokovic defeated by Nadal in French Open semifinal\".",
        "\"Dubai Tennis Championships: Novak Djokovic beats Stefanos Tsitsipas in final\".",
        "\"Novak Djokovic beats Carlos Alcaraz in 'epic' Australian Open quarterfinal\".",
        "\"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win Rome Masters\".",
        "\"Novak Djokovic makes history by beating Dominic Thiem to win eighth Australian Open\".",
        "\"Novak Djokovic rallies to beat Stefanos Tsitsipas in epic French Open final\".",
        "\"Novak Djokovic wins the US Open for his 24th Grand Slam title by beating Daniil Medvedev\".",
        "\"US Open 2011: Novak Djokovic beats Roger Federer in five sets\".",
        "\"US Open 2015: Novak Djokovic beats Roger Federer in final\".",
        "\"Why Novak Djokovic Was Blocked From Entering Australia\".",
        ", Djokovic defeated Jannik Sinner to advance to his 11th final at Melbourne Park, becoming the oldest finalist down under at the age of 38[318",
        "- \"ATP Finals 2023 results: Novak Djokovic beats Jannik Sinner to win title\".",
        "- \"ATP Finals results 2023: Novak Djokovic beats Carlos Alcaraz to set up Jannik Sinner final\".",
        "- \"Australian Open 2019: Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win record seventh title\".",
        "- \"Australian Open: Novak Djokovic beats Dominic Thiem to win 17th Grand Slam\".",
        "- \"Beaten Novak Djokovic says Rafael Nadal can be 'best player ever'.",
        "- \"Djokovic Beats Ferrer to Win Paris Masters Title\".",
        "- \"Djokovic Beats Tsitsipas For Madrid Title, Tying Nadal's Masters 1000 Record\".",
        "- \"Djokovic beats Alcaraz in Australian Open classic, reaches SFs for 12th time\".",
        "- \"Djokovic beats Del Potro in Rome\".",
        "- \"Djokovic beats cramping Alcaraz, into French final\".",
        "- \"Djokovic beats del Potro to win Shanghai Masters\".",
        "- \"Djokovic wins 6th Key Biscayne title by beating Nishikori\".",
        "- \"How Djokovic beat Federer in one of the greatest ever Wimbledon finals\".",
        "- \"Indian Wells: Novak Djokovic beaten by Philipp Kohlschreiber in third round\".",
        "- \"Madrid Open: Novak Djokovic beats Kei Nishikori in round one\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic Beats Rafael Nadal In Epic 2012 Australian Open Final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic Saves 2 M.P. To Beat Roger Federer In Historic Final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beaten by Grigor Dimitrov at Madrid Open\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Carlos Alcaraz to win Olympic tennis gold and seal 'Golden Slam'.",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Del Potro to reach Wimbledon final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Denis Shapovalov to win fifth Paris Masters title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Juan Martín del Potro in epic Wimbledon semi-final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Milos Raonic to retain Paris Masters title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal at the Rome Masters – as it happened\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal in China Open final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal in French Open quarter-finals\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to reach Monte Carlo Open final\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win Italian Open in Rome\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win Monte Carlo Masters title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Rafael Nadal to win Wimbledon men's title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Roger Federer to win ATP World title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Stanislas Wawrinka to reach Australian Open final – as it happened\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Tomas Berdych to win Monte Carlo title\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic beats Tomas Berdych to win fifth China Open\".",
        "- \"Novak Djokovic wins ninth Australian Open by beating Daniil Medvedev\".",
        "- \"US Open 2023 results: Novak Djokovic wins 24th major by beating Daniil Medvedev\".",
        "0. Djokovic then claimed his sixth Australian Open, beating Roger Federer in the semifinals and Andy Murray in the final.[179]",
        "After an early exit at the Monte-Carlo Masters,[183] Djokovic won the Madrid Open, beating Murray in the final.[184]",
        "At Australian Open, Nadal progressed to his fifth Australian Open final without losing a set, then won only eight games against Novak Djokovic, which was Nadal's first straight-sets defeat in a major final.[311]",
        "At Monte Carlo he lost to Novak Djokovic in straight sets in the semi finals,[266] at Barcelona he lost to Fognini in the quarterfinals[267] and at Madrid he lost the final to Andy Murray in straight sets, resulting in his dropping out of the top five for the first time since 2005.[268][269]",
        "At Wimbledon, Djokovic defeated Del Potro in a historic semifinal lasting 4 hours and 44 minutes,[149] but lost the final to Murray in straight sets.",
        "At Wimbledon, Djokovic reached his 9th final but lost to Alcaraz in five sets, ending a 34-match winning streak at Wimbledon.[286]",
        "At Wimbledon, Djokovic won a five-hour quarterfinal over Marcos Baghdatis before retiring in the semifinals against Nadal due to elbow issues.[65][66]",
        "At the 2020 Summer Olympics, Djokovic sought a gold medal, but lost to Alexander Zverev in the semifinals and to Pablo Carreño Busta in the bronze match.[253]",
        "At the 2025 Miami Open, Djokovic beat lucky loser Camilo Ugo Carabelli in the third round to claim his record 411th career main draw win at the Masters 1000 level, surpassing Nadal's previous record of 410.[309]",
        "At the Australian Open, Djokovic reached the semifinals but lost to world No. 4 Jannik Sinner in four sets, ending his 33-match win streak at the event and marking his first semifinal defeat there.",
        "At the Australian Open, Nadal won his semi-final match against Roger Federer to set up a third successive major final against Novak Djokovic, which he lost in a five-set epic that lasted 5 hours and 53 minutes, the longest Grand Slam final match (by duration) in history.[207]",
        "At the French Open, Djokovic defeated world No. 1 Carlos Alcaraz in the semis and beat Casper Ruud in the final to win a record-breaking 23rd major, becoming the first man to achieve a triple Career Grand Slam.[284",
        "At the French Open, Djokovic dropped only two sets en route to the final but lost to Nadal in four sets, his first loss to him after four wins.[157]",
        "At the French Open, Djokovic, then world No. 63, defeated ninth seed Fernando González en route to his first Grand Slam quarterfinal,[52] where, due to issues with his back, he retired against Rafael Nadal after two sets in their first career meeting, launching their historic rivalry.[53]",
        "At the French Open, Nadal won his semi-final match against Ferrer to set up another final against Novak Djokovic.",
        "At the US Open, Djokovic defeated Juan Martín del Potro in straight sets, winning his third US Open and 14th major title overall.[207]",
        "At the US Open, Djokovic saved two match points at 4-5 in the fifth set before beating Federer in the semi-finals,[117] but lost to Nadal in the final in four sets.[118]",
        "Both players met again in the quarterfinals of 2025 Australian Open, in which Djokovic won in four sets[377] and in the semifinals of 2025 US Open, in which Alcaraz won in straight sets.",
        "Djokovic began the year at the Hopman Cup alongside fellow Serbian Jelena Janković, where they reached the finals, but ultimately lost to the United States in the decisive mixed doubles rubber.[72]",
        "Djokovic defeated Zverev in five sets in the semifinals.",
        "Djokovic defended his title at Wimbledon, beating Roger Federer in a record 4-hour 57-minute five-set final.",
        "Djokovic ended the year by winning the 2013 ATP World Tour Finals, beating Nadal in the final.[153]",
        "Djokovic is the player with the most victories over Federer and the only player to beat Federer multiple times at his most successful major tournaments: four times at the Australian Open, three times at the US Open, three times at the Year-end Championship, and most notably, three times in the final of Wimbledon Championships. Their",
        "Djokovic opened the year with his 92nd title at the Adelaide International, saving a championship point to beat Sebastian Korda.",
        "Djokovic reached the final of the Gerry Weber Open on grass but lost to Tommy Haas, and then suffered another defeat to Haas in the quarterfinals of Wimbledon.[101][102]",
        "Djokovic received an exemption from Tennis Australia and the Department of Health (Victoria), citing a positive COVID-19 test on 16 December 2021.[257]",
        "Djokovic rounded off the season by winning his first year-end championship title at the Tennis Masters Cup in Shanghai in November, beating Nikolay Davydenko",
        "Djokovic then beat top seed Roger Federer in straight sets in the final of the Cincinnati Open and thus became the first singles player to complete the Career Golden Masters.[206",
        "Djokovic then defeated Kevin Anderson in the final in straight sets to win his fourth Wimbledon title and 13th overall major title, and returned to the top 10 in the rankings.[205",
        "Djokovic then lost to John Isner in the semifinals of Indian Wells but retained his Miami title by defeating Murray.",
        "Djokovic then participated at the Shanghai Rolex Masters and won his 4th title at the tournament and 2nd Masters title of the year, beating Borna Ćorić in the final.",
        "Djokovic then reached the Rolex Paris Masters final as the defending champion, but lost to Holger Rune, which was the first time he lost a Masters final after winning the first set.[279]",
        "Djokovic then reached the final of the Paris Masters, where he defeated Murray in straight sets, taking his fourth title there and a record sixth ATP Masters tournament in one year.[176]",
        "Djokovic then won the Cincinnati Open, beating Alcaraz in 3 hours and 49 minutes in the longest best-of-three-set ATP final, hailed as one of the greatest matches ever.[287]",
        "Djokovic then won their next match at the 2011 Wimbledon semifinals to advance to his first final there, claiming the world No. 1 ranking for the first time in the process.[355]",
        "Djokovic was a finalist at the US Open, where he lost to Nadal in four sets.[150]",
        "Djokovic won his second Wimbledon title by defeating Federer in five sets in the final, reclaiming the world No. 1 ranking.[158]",
        "Djokovic won in 5 hours and 53 minutes, which was the longest major final and longest match in Australian Open history.",
        "Djokovic won the French Open, defeating Murray in four sets, completing the historic Nole Slam.[186][187]",
        "Djokovic won the next four matches before he lost to del Potro at the 2013 Indian Wells Masters, where the Argentine made his second career Masters final.",
        "Djokovic's Grand Slam debut came at the 2005 Australian Open, followed by his first Slam win at the French Open.[10]: 89–91 That year, he also reached the third round at both Wimbledon[10]: 91 and the US Open, where he beat Gaël Monfils and Mario Ančić.[46]",
        "Djokovic's next tournament was the Indian Wells Open, where he suffered a second-round defeat to lucky loser Botic van de Zandschulp – the 2nd year in a row where he lost to a lucky loser at the same tournament, following Luca Nardi.",
        "Federer served for the match and had two match points in the US Open semi-finals, but Djokovic won in five sets.[130]",
        "Following Nadal's withdrawal from the Paris Masters, Djokovic regained the No. 1 ranking, but lost to unseeded Karen Khachanov in the final.",
        "He won his 4th hard court title of the year, defeating Djokovic in the US Open final to achieve the Summer Slam and clinch the US Open Series.[245",
        "However, Djokovic's quest for a record-extending 25th major title ended in the final, where he was defeated by Carlos Alcaraz.",
        "In 2017, Djokovic suffered from an elbow injury that weakened his results until the 2018 Wimbledon Championships, where he won the title while ranked No. 21 in the world.",
        "In 2018, Djokovic defeated del Potro in three close sets in the final of the US Open, which was the first Grand Slam final for del Potro since his 2009 US Open victory.",
        "In April, Djokovic clinched his second Monte-Carlo Masters by beating Tomáš Berdych in the final,[168] and thus became the first man to win the first three ATP Masters 1000 titles of the season.[169]",
        "In the 2013 Australian Open fourth round, Djokovic won 12–10 in a fifth set, with the match being considered one of",
        "In the second-longest Wimbledon semifinal to date, Djokovic beat Nadal in five sets played over two days.[204]",
        "In their first quarterfinal-level meeting at the Australian Open, Djokovic prevailed in four sets to retain his unbeaten record against Alcaraz on hardcourt and deny his hopes of achieving the Career Grand Slam.[262]",
        "Later that year, Djokovic beat Wawrinka at the Cincinnati Masters and Paris Masters.[349]",
        "Nadal lost to Djokovic in the quarterfinals of the French Open, ending his winning streak of 39 consecutive victories in Paris since his 2009 defeat by Robin Söderling.[271]",
        "Nadal won his 13th French Open, beating Novak Djokovic in straight sets in the final, only losing seven games.",
        "On the other hand, notable players who have won multiple Grand Slam events and have won the French Open, includes Rafael Nadal, Björn Borg, Steffi Graf, Ivan Lendl, Monica Seles, Novak Djokovic, Mats Wilander, Serena Williams, Stan Wawrinka, Justine Henin and Chris Evert, showing proof of their great versatility.",
        "Pat Cash emphasized that Djokovic is one of two players who beat Rafael Nadal at the French Open, which he considers to be \"the biggest challenge in tennis\".[591]",
        "Tennis pundits have classified many of Djokovic's matches as some of the greatest contests ever, such as the 2012 Australian Open final, in which he beat Nadal in five long and gruelling sets.[323][601]",
        "The pair have played some notable matches, including the final of the 2023 ATP Finals, which Djokovic won,[379] the 2024 Australian Open semifinal, which Sinner won in four sets,[380] and the 2024 Shanghai Masters final, which Sinner won in straight sets.[381]",
        "The second set of the 2023 US Open, which Djokovic eventually won in a tiebreaker after a grueling 104-minute battle, was one of the longest sets in US Open history.[363]",
        "The two contested the longest major final ever played at the 2012 Australian Open, where Djokovic won in five sets after 5 hours and 53 minutes.[323][324][325]",
        "Their final major meeting was in the second round of the 2019 Australian Open, which Djokovic won in straight sets.[353]",
        "Their first meeting was in the final of the 2008 Australian Open, which Djokovic won in four sets to win his first major singles title.[353]",
        "Their next encounter was at the 2026 Australian Open semi-final, where Djokovic won in five sets, ending his losing streak against Sinner.[318]",
        "They met again in the quarterfinals of the 2012 French Open, which Djokovic won in five sets after over four hours.[356]",
        "Three weeks later, on August 4, Djokovic defeated Alcaraz in the Olympics final held at Roland Garros.",
        "Three weeks later, on August 4, Djokovic defeated Alcaraz in the Olympics final on Court Philippe Chatrier.",
        "[The first time 15-year-old Novak Djokovic beat 16-year-old Gaël Monfils was in La Baule].",
        "and Slam match came at the 2019 Australian Open 4th round, which Djokovic won in 4 sets.",
        "last final was at the 2019 Wimbledon, where Djokovic won in five sets in the longest final in Wimbledon history.[334][335]",
        "st final without dropping a set and then beat Novak Djokovic to complete his first Career Grand Slam while becoming the second male after Andre Agassi to complete a Career Golden Slam.[177]",
        "the best ever played;[345] at the 2013 US Open semifinals, Djokovic won 6–4 in the fifth set; at the 2014 Australian Open quarterfinals, Wawrinka won 9–7 in the fifth.[346]" ;
